sections.title: How the population has changed in North Northamptonshire
sections.label: Select another area to see how the population has changed

sections.content: In 2020, North Northamptonshire was the third largest local authority in the East Midlands, with a total population of 350,448. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in the East Midlands, 2002-2020
Population density in North Northamptonshire
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in North Northamptonshire was 355 people per square kilometre, which was more than the East Midlands (311), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in the East Midlands, 2020
Median age in North Northamptonshire
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in North Northamptonshire was 42 years, which was older than the East Midlands (41 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
